COVID Wastewater Surveillance for Western Massachusetts

Regional Concentration and Wastewater Viral Activity Level

From 2024-04-12 to 2025-04-11
Current WVA level: moderate
Current WVA score: 5.7

The above figure shows the regional wastewater COVID concentration for 9 sewer systems in Berkshire, Hampden, Hampshire, and Franklin counties. The trend line is a smoothed conditional mean and each point is an individual system report. Trend line and individual reports are each weighted by population and reporting interval. WVA levels are based on the CDC methodology linked below, but use population-weighted statistics, and the 1 year baseline is updated each time the WVA is calculated.

County-level Concentration and Wastewater Viral Activity Level

The above figure shows county-level wastewater COVID concentration for 9 sewer systems in Berkshire, Hampden, Hampshire, and Franklin counties. WVA levels, trend line, and system reports are weighted by population and reporting interval, as described above. Blue annotations indicate date of most recent report.

Concentration for Individual Sewer Systems and Wastewater Viral Activity Level

The above figure shows reported concentration data from individual systems with a smoothed conditional mean. Gaps of longer than one week are not modeled. Blue annotations indicate date of most recent report.

Data Sources
CDC methodology: https://www.cdc.gov/nwss/about-data.html#data-method
Wastewater data access: https://www.mass.gov/info-details/wastewater-surveillance-reporting
Population weights are from various sources (EPA estimates whenever available).
